[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_hfvov")
questions_data = "#1
What does a blockchain mainly consist of?
<y> A series of connected blocks with data and encrypted hashes
<n> A centralized database
<n> A collection of unrelated files
<n> A traditional database with additional security
<e>

#2
What happens if someone tries to change data in a previous block of the blockchain?
<n> The change is automatically accepted by other participants
<y> The hash of that block changes, breaking the chain and making the change obvious
<n> Only the administrator can notice the change
<n> The blockchain automatically restores itself
<e>

#3
Is the transaction history in a blockchain known to every participant?
<y> Yes
<n> No
<n> Depends on the context
<e>

#4
Why use a license?
<y> To give permission to others to use your work under certain conditions
<n> To automatically make your work public and free
<n> To permanently prohibit the use of your work
<n> To transfer your work to the government
<e>

#5
What is open-source?
<n> A program whose source code is publicly available for viewing and modification
<y> A program that is always free and cannot be sold
<n> A program that can only be used in educational institutions
<n> A program owned by the UN
<e>

#6
How do you create a variable in C++?
<y> int x = 10;
<n> variable x = 10;
<n> declare int x = 10;
<n> x := 10
<e>

#7
How do you read a number in C++?
<n> cin << x;
<y> cin >> x;
<n> cout << x;
<n> cout >> x;
<e>

#8
How do you output a number in C++?
<n> cin << x;
<n> cin >> x;
<y> cout << x;
<n> cout >> x;
<e>

#9
How do you calculate the sum of two variables a and b?
<n> sum = \"a\" + \"b\";
<y> sum = a + b;
<y> sum = b + a;
<y> x = a + b;
<e>

#10
What is a valid IP address?
<y> 192.168.104.1;
<y> 0.0.0.0;
<n> 256.257.258;
<y> 1.2.3.4;
<e>

#11
What is DNS?
<n> A protocol for automatically assigning IP addresses to devices
<y> A system that translates domain names into IP addresses
<n> A unique hardware address of a network adapter
<n> A protocol for encrypting data on a network
<e>

#12
What does DHCP do?
<y> Automatically assigns IP addresses to devices on a network
<n> Translates domain names into IP addresses
<n> Is a permanent hardware address of a device
<n> Protects the network from viruses and malware
<e>

#13
How do you swap the first two letters of a string stored in the variable text?
<y> Create a temporary variable
<n> Use text[1] = text[2]
<y> Use text[0] = text[1]
<e>

#14
What is NOT an operating system?
<n> Windows
<n> Android
<n> Linux
<y> Lenovo
<e>

#15
Which statements are correct?
<n> 1 kilobyte (KB) equals 1024 bytes
<y> 1 mebibyte (MiB) equals 1024 kilobytes
<y> 1 gigabyte (GB) equals 1000 megabytes
<y> 1 kibibyte (KiB) equals 1024 bytes
<e>

#16
What is a correct statement in pseudocode?
<y> DECLARE Number : INTEGER
<n> READ Number
<n> WRITE Number
<n> Number = 10
<e>

#17
What is the correct binary representation of the number 35?
<y> 100011
<n> 101100
<n> 101001
<n> 011011

#18
What is the correct hex representation of the binary number 1001 0001 0011 1111
<y> 913F
<n> AB39
<n> 9C67
<n> A139"
